{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775824123625,"sessionID":"ses_288a58108ffeS1DUsDMwJC33nz","part":{"id":"prt_d775a89d3001GX5jJLQA0xELzG","messageID":"msg_d775a7fde001q5u630YDLIzDCe","sessionID":"ses_288a58108ffeS1DUsDMwJC33nz","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_918561f5abd742cba4ec5c1c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project layout (top-level directories and key files)\n2. The pkg/workloadmanager module - all files, their contents, and how they're organized\n3. Any existing sandbox-related code, garbage collection, or cleanup mechanisms\n4. How tasks/checklists are typically structured in this project (look for existing tasks.md files or similar)\n5. Any existing ST-3 stage documentation or design docs related to AR-008\n6. Testing patterns used in the project\n7. Any configuration or scheduling mechanisms already in place\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- The full directory tree of the project (at least 3 levels deep)\n- Key files in pkg/workloadmanager with brief descriptions\n- Any existing GC, cleanup, or scheduling code\n- Existing tasks.md or similar checklist patterns\n- Testing conventions (test file naming, frameworks used)\n- Any relevant interfaces or types that would be involved in sandbox GC","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_288a55b68ffe49iRJDbV7z10x1 (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the AgentCube project. Here is the full summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive AgentCube Project Analysis\n\n### 1. Full Directory Tree (3+ levels deep)\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n├── .sdd_prompt.md                          # SDD (Spec-Driven Development) prompt template\n├── changes/                                # All AR (Architecture Request) change directories\n│   ├── AR-001/                             # (design.md, proposal.md, tasks.md)\n│   ├── AR-002/                             # (delta-spec.md, design.md, proposal.md, tasks.md)\n│   ├── AR-003/                             # (delta-spec.md, design.md, proposal.md, tasks.md)\n│   ├── AR-004/                             # (delta-spec.md, design.md, proposal.md, tasks.md)\n│   ├── AR-005/                             # Sandbox Creation (delta-spec.md, design.md, proposal.md, tasks.md)\n│   ├── AR-006/                             # (delta-spec.md, design.md, proposal.md, tasks.md)\n│   ├── AR-007/                             # Reconciler Controller (delta-spec.md, design.md, proposal.md, tasks.md)\n│   └── AR-008/                             # Sandbox GC (design.md, proposal.md, tasks.md)\n├── ci-cd/                                  # CI/CD design + spec\n├── cli-toolkit/                            # CLI toolkit design + spec\n├── client-go/                              # Generated Kubernetes client-go code\n│   ├── clientset/                          # Clientset + fake client\n│   ├── informers/                          # Externalversions informers\n│   └── listers/                            # Runtime v1alpha1 listers\n├── code-execution/                         # Code execution design + spec\n├── coverage.out                            # Existing coverage output\n├── delta-spec.md                           # AR-008 Delta Spec (detailed requirements)\n├── deployment/                             # Deployment design + spec + client-go docs\n├── design.md                               # AR-003 design doc (shared types extraction)\n├── go.mod                                  # Module: github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube, Go 1.25.0\n├── go.sum\n├── idle-cleanup/                           # Agentd idle cleanup design + spec\n├── integrations/                           # Integration design + spec\n├── pkg/\n│   ├── apis/\n│   │   └── runtime/v1alpha1/               # Kubernetes CRD type definitions\n│   │       ├── agent_type.go               # AgentRuntime CRD types\n│   │       ├── agent_type_test.go\n│   │       ├── codeinterpreter_types.go    # CodeInterpreter CRD types\n│   │       ├── codeinterpreter_types_test.go\n│   │       ├── constants.go                # Shared constants\n│   │       ├── constants_test.go\n│   │       ├── doc.go                      # Package documentation + codegen markers\n│   │       ├── groupversion_info.go        # GroupVersion, SchemeBuilder, Kind constants\n│   │       ├── groupversion_info_test.go\n│   │       ├── shared_types.go             # ProtocolType, TargetPort, AuthModeType\n│   │       ├── shared_types_test.go\n│   │       └── zz_generated.deepcopy.go    # Auto-generated DeepCopy methods\n│   └── workloadmanager/\n│       ├── handler/                        # HTTP handlers + lifecycle management\n│       │   ├── constants.go                # GVRs, Kind constants, labels, annotations, defaults\n│       │   ├── models.go                   # Request/Response models, SandboxInfo, Store interface\n│       │   ├── sandbox_create.go           # Sandbox creation handlers (AgentRuntime + CodeInterpreter)\n│       │   ├── sandbox_delete.go           # Sandbox deletion handlers\n│       │   ├── sandbox_delete_test.go      # Delete handler + mockStore tests\n│       │   ├── sandbox_lifecycle.go        # GC loop, TTL expiry, status/list/extend endpoints\n│       │   └── sandbox_lifecycle_test.go   # Lifecycle manager tests (696 lines)\n│       ├── reconciler/                     # K8s informer-based reconciler\n│       │   ├── agentruntime.go             # AgentRuntime reconciliation logic\n│       │   ├── codeinterpreter.go          # CodeInterpreter reconciliation logic\n│       │   ├── event_handlers.go           # Informer Add/Update/Delete callbacks\n│       │   ├── metrics.go                  # PrometheusMetricsRecorder\n│       │   ├── pod.go                      # Pod reconciliation (IP update)\n│       │   ├── reconciler.go               # SandboxReconciler struct + Run() method\n│       │   ├── sync.go                     # syncHandler + workqueue processing\n│       │   └── types.go                    # Constants, Store/MetricsRecorder interfaces, ReconcilerDeps\n│       └── response/                       # HTTP response utilities\n│           ├── response.go                 # JSON/Error/Created helpers\n│           └── response_test.go\n├── project.md                              # Project overview (architecture, tech stack, conventions)\n├── python-sdk/                             # Python SDK design + spec\n├── sandbox-orchestration/                  # Sandbox orchestration design + spec\n├── session-routing/                        # Session routing design + spec\n├── session-store/                          # Session store (Redis/Valkey) design + spec\n├── testing/\n│   └── agentcube_tdd_manifest.md           # TDD test contract for all modules\n├── test_spec.md                            # Test specification\n└── delta-spec.md                           # AR-008 detailed delta spec (393 lines)\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. Key Files in `pkg/workloadmanager` with Descriptions\n\n| File | Path | Description |\n|------|------|-------------|\n| **constants.go** | `handler/constants.go` | Defines GVR constants (AgentRuntimeGVR, CodeInterpreterGVR, SandboxGVR, SandboxClaimGVR), Kind constants, label/annotation keys, and default values (DefaultSandboxTTL=8h, DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout=15m) |\n| **models.go** | `handler/models.go` | Core data models: `CreateSandboxRequest`, `CreateSandboxResponse`, `EntryPoint`, `SandboxInfo` (SessionID, SandboxName, Namespace, Kind, PodIP, CreatedAt, ExpiresAt, Status), `SandboxStatus`, and the `Store` interface |\n| **sandbox_create.go** | `handler/sandbox_create.go` | `SandboxCreateHandler` with `CreateAgentRuntimeSandbox()` and `CreateCodeInterpreterSandbox()` methods. Handles CR building, Pod IP resolution, entry point construction, rollback on failure, and auth-aware client selection. 693 lines. |\n| **sandbox_delete.go** | `handler/sandbox_delete.go` | `SandboxDeleteHandler` with `DeleteSandbox()` (by session) and `DeleteSandboxByName()` methods. Handles GVR resolution and Store cleanup. 216 lines. |\n| **sandbox_lifecycle.go** | `handler/sandbox_lifecycle.go` | `LifecycleManager` with GC ticker loop (`runCleanupLoop`), `cleanupExpiredSandboxes()`, `isExpired()`, `deleteSandbox()`, `resolveGVR()`, plus HTTP endpoints: `GetSandboxStatus`, `ListSandboxes`, `ExtendSandboxTTL`. Uses `log.Printf` (needs migration to `slog` per AR-008). 343 lines. |\n| **sandbox_lifecycle_test.go** | `handler/sandbox_lifecycle_test.go` | Comprehensive tests for LifecycleManager: default values, expiry logic, Start/Stop idempotency, TTL extension validation, HTTP endpoint tests, cleanup tests, boundary conditions. 696 lines. |\n| **sandbox_delete_test.go** | `handler/sandbox_delete_test.go` | Tests for delete handler + `mockStore` implementation (in-memory map-based Store). 387 lines. |\n| **response/response.go** | `response/response.go` | HTTP response helpers: `JSON()`, `Created()`, `Error()`, `ErrorWithID()` with `SuccessResponse`/`ErrorResponse` wrappers. |\n| **reconciler/types.go** | `reconciler/types.go` | Constants (resource types, results, error types, status values), `Store` interface (different signature from handler's), `MetricsRecorder` interface, `ReconcilerDeps`. |\n| **reconciler/reconciler.go** | `reconciler/reconciler.go` | `SandboxReconciler` struct + `NewSandboxReconciler()` constructor, `Run()` method with informer startup, cache sync, worker goroutines, and graceful shutdown. |\n| **reconciler/event_handlers.go** | `reconciler/event_handlers.go` | Informer event callbacks for AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter, and Pod (Add/Update/Delete). Handles tombstone (`DeletedFinalStateUnknown`) correctly. |\n| **reconciler/sync.go** | `reconciler/sync.go` | `syncHandler()` dispatches to AR/CI/Pod reconcilers. `processNextWorkItem()` handles workqueue with exponential backoff (5s-5min, max 15 retries). |\n| **reconciler/metrics.go** | `reconciler/metrics.go` | `PrometheusMetricsRecorder` with nil-safe methods. Metrics: `reconcile_total`, `reconcile_duration_seconds`, `reconcile_errors_total`, `workqueue_depth`, `workqueue_adds_total`. |\n| **reconciler/pod.go** | `reconciler/pod.go` | `reconcilePod()` updates SandboxInfo PodIP when Pod enters Running state. |\n| **reconciler/agentruntime.go** | `reconciler/agentruntime.go` | `reconcileAgentRuntime()` - reconciles AgentRuntime CR state with Store. |\n| **reconciler/codeinterpreter.go** | `reconciler/codeinterpreter.go` | `reconcileCodeInterpreter()` - reconciles CodeInterpreter CR state with Store. |\n\n---\n\n### 3. Existing GC, Cleanup, and Scheduling Code\n\n**Currently implemented GC (in `sandbox_lifecycle.go`):**\n\n1. **TTL-based expiry cleanup** (existing):\n   - `LifecycleManager.runCleanupLoop()` - runs on a `time.Ticker` with `CheckInterval` (default 5 minutes)\n   - `cleanupExpiredSandboxes()` - lists all sandboxes from Store, checks `isExpired()` for each\n   - `isExpired()` - checks `ExpiresAt` first, falls back to `CreatedAt + DefaultTTL` (default 8 hours)\n   - `deleteSandbox()` - deletes K8s CR via dynamic client, then removes from Store\n   - Uses `log.Printf` (not structured logging)\n\n2. **Agentd idle cleanup** (separate component, in `idle-cleanup/`):\n   - Independent controller-runtime reconciler watching Sandbox CRs\n   - Reads `last-activity-time` annotation\n   - 15-minute `SessionExpirationTimeout`\n   - Requeues with `time.Until(expirationTime)` for precision\n\n3. **What is MISSING (AR-008 scope):**\n   - Idle timeout cleanup in GC loop (no `LastActivityAt` field on `SandboxInfo`)\n   - Orphan CR scanning (CRs in K8s but not in Store)\n   - Ghost entry scanning (Store entries with no corresponding K8s CR)\n   - GC Prometheus metrics\n   - Structured logging (`slog` instead of `log.Printf`)\n\n**Scheduling mechanisms:**\n- `LifecycleManager`: Simple `time.Ticker`-based loop with `Start(ctx)`/`Stop()` pattern, mutex-protected `running` flag\n- `SandboxReconciler`: Kubernetes informer-based event-driven reconciliation with `workqueue.RateLimitingInterface` (exponential backoff: 5s initial, 5min max, 15 retries)\n\n---\n\n### 4. Tasks/Checklist Patterns\n\nEach AR (Architecture Request) in `changes/AR-XXX/` follows a consistent 4-document pattern:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| **proposal.md** | High-level overview, purpose, scope (in/out), impact analysis, alternative solutions, acceptance criteria |\n| **design.md** | Detailed architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, test strategy, implementation phases |\n| **delta-spec.md** | Formal requirements in Given/When/Then scenario format |\n| **tasks.md** | Granular task breakdown with checkbox items (T-001.01, T-001.02, etc.), each with acceptance criteria |\n\n**Task format pattern** (from AR-007, the most complete example):\n```markdown\n## T-001: Task Title\n- [ ] T-001.01 Specific sub-task description\n- [ ] T-001.02 Another sub-task\n**验收**: Build/test commands that must pass\n```\n\n**AR-008 tasks.md** is currently a stub (\"待详细拆分\" - \"to be detailed/split\"). The detailed task breakdown exists in `design.md` Section 6 (Implementation Steps, Phases 1-7) and Section 5 (Test Strategy matrices).\n\n---\n\n### 5. AR-008 Stage Documentation\n\n**AR-008 status:**\n- **Stage**: ST-4 (Implementation) per `changes/AR-008/tasks.md`\n- **Files present**: `proposal.md` (145 lines), `design.md` (515 lines), `tasks.md` (14 lines, stub)\n- **Missing**: `delta-spec.md` in the AR-008 directory (but a comprehensive `delta-spec.md` exists at the project root - 393 lines)\n\n**Key AR-008 design decisions:**\n- Enhances existing `LifecycleManager` GC loop (not a new component)\n- Two-layer safety net: AR-007 Reconciler (event-driven, seconds) + AR-008 GC (timer-based, 5 min default)\n- Four cleanup types: TTL expiry (existing), idle timeout (new), orphan CR (new), ghost entry (new)\n- Reuses `reconciler.MetricsRecorder` interface, extends it with GC methods\n- Migrates `log.Printf` to `slog`\n\n---\n\n### 6. Testing Conventions\n\n**Framework**: `github.com/stretchr/testify` (assert + require packages)\n\n**File naming**: `*_test.go` alongside source files (same package, not `_test` package)\n\n**Test patterns observed:**\n1. **Table-driven tests** with `t.Run()` subtests (e.g., `TestLifecycleManager_IsExpired_BoundaryConditions`)\n2. **Mock Store**: `mockStore` struct with in-memory `map[string]*SandboxInfo` implementing the `Store` interface\n3. **Fake K8s clients**: `k8s.io/client-go/dynamic/fake.NewSimpleDynamicClient()`\n4. **Gin test context**: `gin.CreateTestContext(httptest.NewRecorder())` for HTTP handler testing\n5. **Nil-safety tests**: Explicit tests for nil receiver/method behavior\n6. **Boundary condition tests**: Exact expiry, 1-second-before, 1-second-after\n\n**Test coverage requirements** (from TDD manifest and task files):\n- Line coverage >= 80%\n- T/C ratio (test lines / code lines) > 0.4\n- `go test -race` must pass (no data races)\n- Every source file must have a corresponding `*_test.go`\n\n**Existing test files (9 total):**\n- `handler/sandbox_lifecycle_test.go` (696 lines) - most comprehensive\n- `handler/sandbox_delete_test.go` (387 lines) - includes mockStore\n- `response/response_test.go` (110 lines)\n- `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` - 5 test files for API types\n\n---\n\n### 7. Key Interfaces and Types for Sandbox GC\n\n**Core interfaces that GC interacts with:**\n\n```go\n// handler/models.go (693 lines of sandbox_create.go reference this)\ntype Store interface {\n    StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, info *SandboxInfo) error\n    UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, info *SandboxInfo) error\n    GetSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*SandboxInfo, error)\n    DeleteSandbox(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) error\n    ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context) ([]*SandboxInfo, error)\n}\n\n// Current SandboxInfo (needs LastActivityAt per AR-008)\ntype SandboxInfo struct {\n    SessionID    string       `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxName  string       `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    SandboxID    string       `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    WorkloadName string       `json:\"workloadName\"`\n    Namespace    string       `json:\"namespace\"`\n    Kind         string       `json:\"kind\"`\n    PodIP        string       `json:\"podIp,omitempty\"`\n    EntryPoints  []EntryPoint `json:\"entryPoints,omitempty\"`\n    CreatedAt    time.Time    `json:\"createdAt\"`\n    ExpiresAt    time.Time    `json:\"expiresAt\"`\n    Status       string       `json:\"status\"`\n    // MISSING: LastActivityAt time.Time `json:\"lastActivityAt\"`\n}\n\n// Current LifecycleManagerDeps (needs GC fields per AR-008)\ntype LifecycleManagerDeps struct {\n    DynamicClient dynamic.Interface\n    Store         Store\n    CheckInterval time.Duration\n    DefaultTTL    time.Duration\n    // MISSING: DefaultIdleTimeout time.Duration\n    // MISSING: MetricsRecorder GCMetrics\n}\n\n// reconciler/types.go - MetricsRecorder interface (needs GC methods)\ntype MetricsRecorder interface {\n    IncReconcileTotal(resourceType string, result string)\n    ObserveReconcileDuration(resourceType string, duration time.Duration)\n    IncReconcileErrors(resourceType string, errorType string)\n    SetWorkqueueDepth(depth int)\n    IncWorkqueueAdds(resourceType string)\n    // MISSING: IncGCCleanupTotal(reason string)\n    // MISSING: ObserveGCCleanupDuration(duration time.Duration)\n    // MISSING: IncGCCleanupErrors(reason string)\n    // MISSING: ObserveGCCycleDuration(duration time.Duration)\n}\n```\n\n**Key constants already defined** (in `handler/constants.go`):\n- `LabelSessionID = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"`\n- `AnnotationIdleTimeout = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"`\n- `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15` (minutes)\n- `DefaultSandboxTTL = 8` (hours)\n- `AgentRuntimeGVR`, `CodeInterpreterGVR`, `SandboxGVR`, `SandboxClaimGVR`\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_288a55b68ffe49iRJDbV7z10x1","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775823922324,"end":1775824123622}}}}
